name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
notes:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event. 

• This is a drive-thru clinic at South Puget Sound Community College (SPSCC), use the Crosby Blvd entrance. • All minors 16 and 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with warm layers. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
notes: ***1ST & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!! (Nuestra Casa in Partnership with Sunnyside School District) Drive on S. 1st St towards the Yakima County Free Testing Center and turn right onto E Lincoln Ave. Continue east and turn left onto S. 6th St. The vaccination site will be held at the Sunnyside School District, which is next to Washington Elementary School and across the street from St. Joseph Parish church. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 16 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. Conduzca en S. 1st St hacia el Centro de Pruebas Gratuitas del Condado de Yakima y gire a la derecha sobre E Lincoln Ave. Continúe hacia el este y dé vuelta a la izquierda sobre S. 6th St. El sitio de vacunación se llevará a cabo en el Distrito Escolar Sunnyside, que está al lado de la Escuela Primaria Washington y al otro lado de la calle de la iglesia parroquial de St. Joseph. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todas las personas mayores de 16 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel. ***1ST & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!!
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine - COVID Vaccine Clinic
notes:
Please read the following important information below:
***We currently have the ability to provide the 1st dose only of Moderna.***
Please sign up for an appointment time.  

When you arrive to the clinic, please continue to wear your face covering, practice physical distancing and wash your hands frequently to help reduce transmission.

Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. 
Expect to stay for 15 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. 

Due to the limited supplies of vaccines provided to us each week, we are unable to take walk-ins, so please make an appointment. 

***Directions to the Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine:***
Our clinic is located in the Hidden Valley Office Complex.
1) When you arrive at the complex, take either driveway all the way to the back of the building.
2) We are located on the prominent corner at the very back of the building and we have our own private entrance.  Look for the parking lot with the number "2" in a big steel frame.  Do NOT go into the main building for we have a private entrance accessible directly from the parking lot. 
Look for our sign with our logo in the window and a door with the number "C-102" on it, visible from the parking lot.

*If you would like to find out more information about our clinic, please visit our website at www.hawkerhealth.com
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
